28/10/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The EU-financed Stability Pact for Southeast Europe opened a regional corruption fighting office in Sarajevo on Monday (27 October).
The office will train police officers, prosecutors and judges.
It will also organise regional forums for political discussion and initiate relevant legislative amendments.
The United States, France, Germany, Norway, Sweden, Switzerland, the Council of Europe, and the World Bank sponsor the Stability Pact initiative.
(Beta - 28/10/03)
